description: Sum of cubes of unitary divisors of n.
comments: A unitary divisor of n is a divisor d such that GCD(d,n/d)=1.
formula: Dirichlet g.f. zeta(s)*zeta(s-3)/zeta(2s-3). - R. J. Mathar, Mar 04 2011
example: The unitary divisors of 6 are 1, 2, 3 and 6, so a(6) = 252.
prog: (PARI) A034677_vec(len)={        a000012=direuler(p=2,len, 1/(1-X)) ;        a000578=direuler(p=2,len, 1/(1-p^3*X)) ;        a000578x=direuler(p=2,len, 1-p^3*X^2) ;        dirmul(dirmul(a000012,a000578),a000578x)}A034677_vec(70) /* via D.g.f., R. J. Mathar, Mar 05 2011 */
author: _Erich Friedman_
